source.name: Bibliographical Metadata of the Foreign Relations of the United States Series
source.description: The Office of the Historian is responsible, under law, for the preparation and publication of the official historical documentary record of U.S. foreign policy in the Foreign Relations of the United States series.  The dataset that the Office of the Historian is submitting is the raw bibliographical metadata for the nearly 500 volumes in this series published since 1861.  Each record in the dataset contains a volume's title, year of publication, years covered by the volume, summary, and links to websites that offer these volumes online or in print, among other metadata items.
